Subject: [PATCH] fix(ui): make light/professional themes actually visible +
 kill narrow gutters
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0075 — fixes two high-visibility UX bugs reported by user:
  1. "Pressing LIGHT but still shows all dark background"
  2. "Some dark space on left and right why compressing text"

ROOT CAUSE — themes
  ThemeContext sets data-theme on <html> + exposes CSS variables, but
  every dashboard page uses HARDCODED inline-style hex (#0A0E1A,
  #0D1B2E, #1A2840, #F5F7FA, etc.) that ignores CSS variables. So
  clicking LIGHT changed only theme-aware components — the rest stayed
  dark.

  FIX — global override layer in globals.css. When html[data-theme="light"]
  or "professional" is active, [style*="..."] attribute selectors with
  !important override every common hardcoded hex code. Both forms
  matched (hex AND rgb(...) since browsers normalize inline styles).

  Light theme overrides (20+ rules):
    page bg #0A0E1A → #ffffff
    panel bg #0D1B2E / #111B35 → #f7f8fa
    inner panel #1A2840 / #1E2D45 → #f0f3f7
    primary text #F5F7FA → #0f172a
    muted #94A3B8 → #475569
    accent #0F7ABF → #0369a1
    aside / header → light variants

  Professional theme (Bloomberg-terminal black + orange):
    page bg → #000000
    panel → #0f0f0f
    blue accents → orange (#ffa500 / #ff8800)
    body font → "Roboto Mono"

ROOT CAUSE — narrow gutters
  News page had maxWidth:1000, multibagger maxWidth:1100, earnings-AI
  maxWidth:1200, watchlists maxWidth:1200. On wide screens this created
  200-400px of empty dark space on each side while text was compressed
  in the middle.

  FIX — bumped all to maxWidth:1800 in source AND added a global CSS
  selector `main > div[style*="margin: 0 auto"] { max-width: 1800px !important }`
  so any future page with a narrow constraint also stretches.

UI-only patch — no API contract changes, cache key not bumped.
